    "description": "\nScattered thunderstorms are expected to affect much of Lake Superior this afternoon through this evening. These thunderstorms may produce wind gusts up to 35 knots, frequent lightning and potentially small hail.\n\n###\n\nPlease continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. For more information monitor Canadian Coast Guard radio or Weatheradio stations.\n",
    "instruction": "\nVessels without lightning protection should make their way to shore immediately. Mariners are advised to prepare for potential squalls. Vulnerable vessels are most at risk and should seek safe harbour if underway.\n",
